title: High-school football | Roundup: Licking Heights rallies to beat Watkins Memorial
text:
Hilliard Davidson 38, Westland 3 The Columbus Dispatch â€¢ Saturday October 3, 2015 12:44 AM 
Licking Heights 31, Watkins Memorial 22: Licking Heights (5-1, 1-0) scored 21 consecutive points on the way to a win over visiting Watkins Memorial (4-2, 0-1) Friday night in the Licking County League Buckeye Division. With Licking Heights trailing 16-3, Joey Harrell, who led the Hornets with 84 yards rushing, scored from 11 yards out. Gabe Caldwell threw a pair of touchdown passes in the third quarter, and Adrien Hammonds added a 1-yard TD run in the fourth. Westley Brandon had 197 yards passing and three touchdowns for Watkins. Hartley 31, St. Charles 10: Quri Hickman rushed for 151 yards and three TDs to lead Hartley (4-2) past visiting St. Charles (3-3) in a nonleague game. Rian Henderson returned the opening kickoff 98 yards for Hartley, which rushed for 264 yards on 52 attempts. Allen Smith had a 1-yard TD run for St. Charles. Highland 22, Centerburg 18: Dakota Bunting ran for two fourth-quarter touchdowns, and Highland (3-3, 3-0) rallied from an 18-7 deficit to defeat host Centerburg (3-3, 2-1) in a Mid-Ohio Athletic Conference Blue Division game. Jonathan Alder 35, Buckeye Valley 20: Sean Sullivan rushed for 204 yards and two TDs on 22 carries, and Jonathan Alder (5-1, 3-0) jumped to a 28-0 lead in beating host Buckeye Valley (3-3, 2-1) in the MOAC Red. Dean Karkut caught TD passes of 34 and 64 yards from Preston Eisnaugle for Alder. Ben Spaulding completed 30 of 50 passes for 339 yards and two late TDs for Buckeye Valley. Licking Valley 56, Lakewood 7: Bailey Hayden, Ethan Fout and Jake Lewis each ran for more than 100 yards, and Licking Valley (4-2, 1-0) gained all of its 543 yards on the ground to defeat host Lakewood (1-4, 0-1) in the LCL Buckeye. Johnstown 35, Northridge 0: Andrew Sayer rushed for three TDs in the first quarter, and Johnstown (6-0, 1-0) had no problems with host Northridge (4-2, 0-1) in the LCL Buckeye.
